org.apache.commons.functor.generator.range

Interface Range<T,S>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements held by this range.
    S - the type of the step of this range.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CharacterRange, DoubleRange, FloatRange, IntegerRange, LongRange, NumericRange

    public interface Range<T,S>
    Represent an interval of elements that varies from the left limit to the right limit. Each limit in this range is an Endpoint. The left and the right limits can be inclusive (bounded, closed) or exclusive (unbounded, open).

    The difference between each element within this range is called step. The step can be positive or negative, displaying whether the range elements are ascending or descending.
